AGENT: REFACTOR
FEATURE: phase4_accessibility_lint
DATE: 2026-03-17
STATUS: DONE
SUMMARY: 1 file fixed — eliminated react-hooks/set-state-in-effect lint error in LoginForm.tsx

ISSUE:
  LoginForm.tsx line 33: setShouldFocusError(false) called inside useEffect body
  violated the react-hooks/set-state-in-effect rule.
  The shouldFocusError boolean state was only ever used as a signal to trigger
  the effect — a pattern that creates an extra render cycle and a lint violation.

FIX:
  Replaced shouldFocusError useState(false) with hasFocusedRef = useRef(false).
  The effect now watches `error` directly (already in state) and uses the ref
  as a guard to prevent re-focusing on re-renders while the same error persists:
    - error transitions null → string: focus fires once, hasFocusedRef = true
    - error persists across re-renders: guard blocks duplicate focus
    - error transitions string → null (setError(null) on new attempt): ref resets
  Removed setShouldFocusError(true) call from handleSubmit; setError() alone
  is sufficient to trigger the effect.

OUTPUT_FILE: src/components/auth/LoginForm.tsx
